comments: Harden (BKN) legally contests Green's (PHI) jump shot attempt.  Any ?high-five? contact after the release of the shot is considered incidental.
Embiid (PHI) legally contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt.  Any ?high-five? contact after the release of the shot is considered incidental.
During the rebound Aldridge (BKN) places his hand on Harris' (PHI) back with little force, and does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
During the rebound, Maxey (PHI) dislodges the ball from Aldridge (BKN) causing the ball to go OOB.
Prior to the ball going OOB, Harris (PHI) makes marginal contact with Durant's (BKN) side that does not cause him to lose control of the ball.
The ball makes contact with Harris' (PHI) right knee and then off of Durant's (BKN) leg before going OOB.  The ball is incorrectly given to the Nets.
Maxey (PHI) and Mills (BKN) engage during the inbound and Mills' reaction is not commensurate with the level of contact as Maxey releases.
Aldridge (BKN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Embiid's (PHI) driving shot attempt.
Green (PHI) establishes himself in a legal guarding position in Durant's (BKN) path and Durant moves through his space.  An offensive foul should have been called.

As Embiid (PHI) turns following the contest, he inadvertently makes contact with Harden's (BKN) face.   Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Embiid (PHI) makes contact with Aldridge's (BKN) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Durant (BKN) makes marginal contact with Harris' (PHI) body that does not affect his SQBR during the driving shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) commits a take foul on Aldridge (BKN).
Mills (BKN) commits a take foul on Curry (PHI).
Curry (PHI) commits a take foul on Durant (BKN).
Embiid (PHI) commits a take foul on Harden (BKN).
Mills (BKN) moves through Curry's (PHI) spaces and makes contact to his lower body that dislodges him from his position.
